{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to target content to the right users at the right time, you need to identify users and send Appcues data about them."}],"metadata":{"title":"Identifying and Managing Users","modules":[{"name":"AppcuesKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Identifying","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Tracking","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/URLSchemeConfiguring","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/AnchoredTooltips","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/PushNotifications","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"],"anchor":"Core-Functionality","title":"Core Functionality","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Identifying Known Users","anchor":"Identifying-Known-Users","level":2},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appcues recommends choosing opaque and hard to guess user IDs, such as a UUID. See the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.appcues.com\/article\/159-faq#choosing-a-user-id"},{"type":"text","text":" for more details about how to choose a User ID."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/identify(userID:properties:)","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is recommended that the application identify a user at moments such as sign in, and also when the app starts up on a cold launch with existing log in credentials. This will ensure that any user properties tied to this user can be kept accurately up to date.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The inverse of identifying is resetting. For example, if a user logs out of your app. Calling "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/reset()","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will disable tracking of screens and events until a user is identified again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you have special security needs and your account has been configured to use the Appcues identity verification feature, follow the steps outlined in the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.appcues.com\/dev-installing-appcues\/identity-verification","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", when calling "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/identify(userID:properties:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Identifying Anonymous Users","anchor":"Identifying-Anonymous-Users","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/anonymous()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The format of anonymous IDs can customized with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/Config\/anonymousIDFactory(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". Anonymous IDs will always be prefixed with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"anon:"},{"text":" by the SDK.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Grouping-Users","text":"Grouping Users","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Associating a user with a group allows you to additionally capture analytics at the group level, and target content to show based upon group membership and properties."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/group(groupID:properties:)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To ensure the most accurate content targeting based upon group information, it’s recommended to supply the group information immediately after a new user is identified.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/appcueskit\/identifying"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit"],["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"]]},"references":{"doc://com.appcues.sdk/documentation/AppcuesKit/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","url":"\/documentation\/appcueskit\/gettingstarted","title":"Getting Started with Appcues iOS SDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initialize the SDK and track events."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"article"},"doc://com.appcues.sdk/documentation/AppcuesKit/Appcues/Config/anonymousIDFactory(_:)":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/appcueskit\/appcues\/config\/anonymousidfactory(_:)","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/Config\/anonymousIDFactory(_:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"anonymousIDFactory"},{"kind":"text","text":"(() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"}],"title":"anonymousIDFactory(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"Set the factory responsible for generating anonymous user ID’s.","type":"text"}]},"https://docs.appcues.com/article/159-faq#choosing-a-user-id":{"url":"https:\/\/docs.appcues.com\/article\/159-faq#choosing-a-user-id","identifier":"